=begin

given two intgers
  -add the two integers together
  -return the sum

given an array of strings
   -create an empty string variable
   -iterate through the length of the array
   -add each index to the string variable

given an array of integers
  -create a new empty array
  -iterate through the array of integers
  -if index is even, add the element to the new array
  -if index is odd, move to the next iteration

given a string and a character
  -split the string into an array of characters
  -set a counter variable equal to zero
  -iterate through the array
    -check if each index it equal to the given character
    -if equal, add + 1 to the counter variable
    -if not equal, move to the next iteration
    -check if counter variable = 3, break and return the current index
    -otherwise return nil

given two number arrays
  -create a new empty array
  -create a counter variable equal to zero
  -create a stop variable equal to sum of array lengths
  -until stop variable = 0
    -if counter variable is even, array1 at index counter = new array at index counter
    -if counter variable is odd, array2 at index counter = new array at index counter
    -counter += 1; stop variable -= 1
  

=end
